WEBVTT

00:11.344 --> 00:13.096
[Jen] You wanna tell us
where you went last night?

00:13.179 --> 00:15.181
-You're not in trouble.
-You're in so much fucking trouble.

00:15.306 --> 00:17.100
I just drove without a license. Who cares?

00:17.183 --> 00:18.560
[Jen] The law. That's who cares.

00:18.643 --> 00:21.146
Do you know what the punishment is
for driving without a license?

00:21.646 --> 00:22.480
What?

00:22.564 --> 00:24.065
-You go to fucking jail.
-A ticket, then--

00:24.149 --> 00:25.316
-Seriously?
-[Jen] Mm-hmm.

00:25.400 --> 00:27.152
You could get your mom
in a lot of trouble, too.

00:27.235 --> 00:28.486
Yeah. So...

00:29.112 --> 00:32.282
Do you want to tell me where you went
on your little joyride?

00:32.490 --> 00:34.159
[stuttering] We didn't really go anywhere.

00:34.242 --> 00:37.120
I picked up Parker around four, then
we drove out to where you found us.

00:37.203 --> 00:38.872
We-- we barely got out of the car.

00:38.955 --> 00:40.957
-Oh, really? You barely got out?
-Mm-hmm.

00:41.041 --> 00:43.960
What were you doing sitting
in a car for five hours?

00:47.213 --> 00:49.090
-Oh, God.
-Okay.

00:49.215 --> 00:50.050
-Oh.
-Give me your phone.

00:50.425 --> 00:51.718
-What?
-[Jen] You heard me.

00:51.801 --> 00:54.179
And go get your laptop
and all your video game shit

00:54.262 --> 00:55.221
and a power drill.

00:55.930 --> 00:56.848
Why?

00:56.931 --> 00:58.558
Because you just lost your bedroom door.

00:58.767 --> 00:59.684
That-- [laughs]

00:59.768 --> 01:01.227
-That's fucking crazy.
-[Jen] You know what?

01:01.311 --> 01:04.272
Until you can prove to me
that you can make good decisions

01:04.355 --> 01:06.357
and that you care about anybody
but yourself,

01:06.441 --> 01:07.692
you are gonna go where I go,

01:07.776 --> 01:09.152
you are gonna do what I do.

01:09.235 --> 01:11.905
No privileges and no fucking fun.

01:11.988 --> 01:13.448
Judy, will you tell her
she's being insane?

01:13.990 --> 01:15.241
I think Jen is your mother,

01:15.325 --> 01:18.036
and you should listen to her
and trust that she knows what she's doing.

01:18.119 --> 01:19.704
-Thank you, Judy.
-You're welcome.

01:19.788 --> 01:22.749
You sure you know what you're doing?
I feel like you're being a little harsh.

01:22.832 --> 01:24.876
Do you really think burning the car
was the best idea?

01:25.210 --> 01:27.629
Charlie's fingerprints were all over it.
What choice did I have?

01:27.712 --> 01:29.881
Don't you think it's like
sending a smoke signal?

01:29.964 --> 01:32.759
Oh, my God. If I have to explain it,
then you're not gonna fucking get it.

01:32.842 --> 01:33.927
-[Henry] Mommy.
-[Jen] Hi.

01:35.386 --> 01:36.471
My stomach hurts.

01:37.097 --> 01:39.224
I don't think I can go
to Holy Harmonies practice.

01:39.307 --> 01:41.559
-[Judy] Aww.
-But, babe, it's your first solo tonight.

01:41.643 --> 01:43.770
Oh, maybe he's a little nervous?

01:44.979 --> 01:48.316
Okay, look. Hen, we all have stuff
that we don't want to do,

01:48.399 --> 01:50.026
but sometimes in life there are have-to's,

01:50.110 --> 01:52.654
and you made a commitment,
so this is a have-to.

01:53.196 --> 01:54.364
Here, for your tummy.

01:55.532 --> 01:56.407
Thanks.

01:56.491 --> 01:57.659
Is that a new necklace?

01:57.742 --> 01:58.743
It's pretty.

01:58.827 --> 02:02.372
Yeah. My new friend gave me the stone,
and then I made the necklace.

02:02.455 --> 02:03.289
[Henry] Cool.

02:04.374 --> 02:05.667
New friend? What new friend?

02:05.750 --> 02:07.252
Michelle. I met her at work.

02:07.335 --> 02:08.294
Oh.

02:09.254 --> 02:11.005
-Happy?
-Fucking ecstatic.

02:11.965 --> 02:13.383
[chimes]

02:15.218 --> 02:16.052
Oh, God.

02:19.264 --> 02:21.266
[both gasp]

02:22.058 --> 02:23.184
-Motherfuck--
-Oh, sh--

02:23.268 --> 02:25.270
[loud crash]

02:25.353 --> 02:26.938
[metal squeaks]

02:28.273 --> 02:30.275
[doorbell rings]

02:31.526 --> 02:34.028
Oh. Hey, Mrs. Harding.

02:34.112 --> 02:35.446
Hi, Parker.

02:35.989 --> 02:38.575
Look, I just wanted
to say I'm really sorry.

02:38.658 --> 02:41.286
I think that we got off
on the wrong foot last night.

02:41.369 --> 02:44.080
[laughs]
Yeah. You were, like, freaking out.

02:44.164 --> 02:45.331
Yeah, that was nothing.

02:45.415 --> 02:47.292
Uh,
that's why I brought you some cupcakes.

02:47.375 --> 02:52.213
Aww, thanks, um, but I don't eat, like,
cupcake dough.

02:52.297 --> 02:55.800
Sure. Uh, actually, you know what?

02:56.217 --> 02:58.178
You posted a picture of Charlie.

02:58.261 --> 02:59.095
Oh, yeah.

02:59.179 --> 03:00.889
He looks like a total snack, right?

03:01.431 --> 03:02.265
Right.

03:02.891 --> 03:03.766
Here's the thing.

03:04.684 --> 03:06.936
Charlie doesn't have a driver's license.

03:07.020 --> 03:11.608
So if anyone saw that picture,
he would get in a lot of trouble.

03:11.691 --> 03:13.443
-Oh, God.
-Yeah.

03:13.526 --> 03:16.529
So I'm gonna need you to, like,
take it down.

03:17.071 --> 03:17.947
Oh.

03:18.656 --> 03:22.118
Tsk. Yeah, see,
I would, because I love Charlie,

03:22.202 --> 03:23.328
but I can't.

03:24.078 --> 03:25.747
Wait, why?

03:25.830 --> 03:26.748
'Cause I get paid.

03:26.998 --> 03:28.833
I'm a micro-influencer, so...

03:29.042 --> 03:31.753
[murmurs] I have no idea
what the fuck you're talking about.

03:31.836 --> 03:35.215
Well, Instagram has, like,
big influencers and small influencers.

03:35.298 --> 03:37.842
This is so fucking embarrassing.

03:38.134 --> 03:40.678
Your mom is just trying to protect you.
She loves you.

03:40.762 --> 03:42.597
Yeah, well,
she's pretty shitty at showing it.

03:43.932 --> 03:44.891
[clears throat]

03:46.809 --> 03:48.519
I lost my virginity in a car.

03:49.437 --> 03:50.313
It was beautiful.

03:50.813 --> 03:51.981
It was a '78 Corvette.

03:52.065 --> 03:53.441
We're not having this conversation.

03:53.524 --> 03:54.400
No? Okay.

03:56.444 --> 03:58.696
Do you like her? Parker.

04:00.198 --> 04:01.115
I don't know.

04:02.617 --> 04:04.744
Whatever. How does anybody know
if they like anybody?

04:04.827 --> 04:05.703
I don't know.

04:07.413 --> 04:08.790
Feel like you...

04:09.958 --> 04:11.417
just like to be around them.

04:13.086 --> 04:16.881
You want to be with them all the time,
and they make you feel safe.

04:17.674 --> 04:18.716
And you can be your...

04:19.968 --> 04:21.386
best self and your...

04:21.886 --> 04:24.597
-when you feel vulnerable--
-Okay, can we not talk anymore?

04:24.681 --> 04:25.515
Yeah.

04:26.724 --> 04:27.558
One more thing.

04:29.185 --> 04:31.646
Please use condoms.
You don't want to get warts.

04:34.607 --> 04:35.817
-Or...
-Yep.

04:35.900 --> 04:38.278
...any other sores down there.

04:38.361 --> 04:40.029
[sighs] Okay.

04:40.113 --> 04:42.782
'Cause if there's oozing,
you're gonna be pretty upset.

04:42.865 --> 04:43.700
[groans]

04:43.783 --> 04:46.786
And so under 800,000 followers is,
like, a whole different pay scale.

04:46.869 --> 04:50.039
Okay, so how much then
for you to take the picture down?

04:50.707 --> 04:51.833
Like, 100 bucks?

04:52.917 --> 04:55.044
That's not a lot of money anymore.
[chuckles]

04:55.128 --> 04:57.380
[murmurs] Oh, fuck you. Um...

04:58.381 --> 04:59.340
Five hundred.

05:00.633 --> 05:02.051
-A thousand dollars.
-[scoffs]

05:02.510 --> 05:04.095
And because you love Charlie,

05:04.178 --> 05:06.764
you will never mention your little outing
to anyone ever.

05:08.599 --> 05:09.559
Okay.

05:09.642 --> 05:10.476
Okay.

05:11.269 --> 05:12.186
Please hold these.

05:17.734 --> 05:18.568
What's...

05:19.193 --> 05:20.111
What are you drawing?

05:21.362 --> 05:22.238
Seriously?

05:22.989 --> 05:23.990
It's a check.

05:26.200 --> 05:27.702
Okay. Uh...

05:27.785 --> 05:28.619
Do you have Venmo?

05:28.703 --> 05:30.038
Do I have what, what?

05:30.413 --> 05:33.541
Oh, you also have to watch out
for chlamydia, gonorrhea,

05:33.624 --> 05:35.835
syphilis, which made
Benjamin Franklin crazy.

05:35.918 --> 05:37.837
I don't know if you know,
but that's what he died of.

05:37.920 --> 05:38.755
-Anyway...
-[Jen sighs]

05:38.838 --> 05:39.881
[Charlie] Oh, thank God.

05:42.091 --> 05:43.134
-How'd that go?
-[Jen sighs]

05:43.676 --> 05:46.429
Expensive,
but she is going to take it down.

05:46.846 --> 05:49.265
Hey, Charlie,
your girlfriend's a little extortionist.

05:49.349 --> 05:50.350
She's not my girlfriend.

05:50.433 --> 05:51.559
She seems to think so.

05:52.018 --> 05:53.186
She said she loved you.

05:53.478 --> 05:55.480
-Oh, Charlie.
-Shit, really?

05:56.606 --> 05:57.482
Char--

05:57.607 --> 06:01.235
Charlie, you need to know that sex is
something different for girls at your age.

06:01.319 --> 06:02.362
At any age.

06:02.445 --> 06:05.281
There are feelings involved.

06:06.032 --> 06:07.784
You just gotta be careful, okay?

06:08.284 --> 06:10.286
I know. Judy told me about warts.

06:11.204 --> 06:13.539
It was part of a larger conversation.

06:13.623 --> 06:16.626
Is that a thing?
Do people even get warts anymore?

06:16.709 --> 06:17.627
There's a vaccine.

06:17.710 --> 06:19.879
-You should get the vaccine.
-[Jen] It's so '70s.

06:19.962 --> 06:21.005
[chiming]

06:21.130 --> 06:22.382
-Oh, shit.
-[Jen] What?

06:24.675 --> 06:26.803
-Why are they calling you?
-I don't know.

06:26.886 --> 06:28.971
-Shouldn't you answer?
-Do I have to?

06:29.597 --> 06:30.932
Miss Hale, thank you for coming.

06:31.015 --> 06:31.849
Of course.

06:32.266 --> 06:33.226
Your hair looks amazing.

06:33.309 --> 06:34.894
-Did you do something different?
-No.

06:35.478 --> 06:37.772
We got some new information pertaining
to Steve Wood.

06:38.231 --> 06:39.065
Oh, you do?

06:39.148 --> 06:42.443
-We've gained access to his phone records.
-Oh!

06:42.527 --> 06:44.153
We've been trying
to piece together a timeline,

06:44.237 --> 06:46.280
and interestingly,
his last calls made were to you.

06:46.781 --> 06:47.615
Were they?

06:47.698 --> 06:50.034
He called you a total of nine times
the night he disappeared.

06:50.118 --> 06:53.663
Oh, that's right.
He called, but I didn't get it.

06:54.038 --> 06:56.165
I just let them go to voicemail.

06:56.249 --> 06:58.000
Hmm. You still have those voicemails?

06:58.334 --> 07:00.503
Hmm. I don't know, I mean, do I?

07:00.586 --> 07:03.339
Miss Hale, we can do this the hard way:
I go to a judge, request a warrant,

07:03.423 --> 07:06.384
but it doesn't look great,
or you could just play me the messages.

07:06.467 --> 07:07.885
-Which do you prefer?
-Neither.

07:07.969 --> 07:09.470
-Neither's not an option.
-Okay.

07:09.554 --> 07:12.348
If there's any information
on those voicemails, I need to know.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.142
-There isn't.
-Prove it.

07:15.435 --> 07:16.978
[exhales]

07:23.234 --> 07:26.404
Do you think that maybe there's somewhere
private that we could listen to them?

07:30.658 --> 07:31.617
[sighs]

07:32.535 --> 07:33.536
[beeps]

07:33.619 --> 07:35.288
[Steve] <i>What the fuck, Judy?</i>

07:35.705 --> 07:37.874
<i>You have some fucking nerve,</i>
<i>you know that? You better call me.</i>

07:37.957 --> 07:40.877
<i>You hear me? Call me,</i> <i>you fucking bitch!</i>

07:43.045 --> 07:45.214
I really appreciate you taking the time
to do this today.

07:45.298 --> 07:46.132
Yeah, well, of course.

07:46.215 --> 07:48.134
But I mean, if you like it,
I would jump on it,

07:48.217 --> 07:49.969
'cause it's not gonna be
on the market for long.

07:50.052 --> 07:51.637
Oh, I'll bet. It's pretty shwanky.

07:51.721 --> 07:53.055
Oh, yeah, it's shwanky.

07:53.389 --> 07:55.141
I mean, yes,
it's more than you wanted to pay,

07:55.224 --> 07:57.810
but it does have a rooftop terrace
with a fire pit,

07:57.894 --> 08:00.271
and of course, the beach is your backyard.

08:00.354 --> 08:03.566
I'm not much of a beach guy.
That's more Steve's deal.

08:03.649 --> 08:06.319
Well, the curtains are remote control,
so you can just shut those

08:06.402 --> 08:08.779
-and not even look out there.
-You know what?

08:08.863 --> 08:10.323
Nothing matters. I'll take it.

08:11.073 --> 08:11.908
-Really?
-Yes.

08:11.991 --> 08:14.327
I just have to get out
of my parents' house.

08:14.410 --> 08:16.704
I have to. The same thing
happens every night.

08:16.787 --> 08:20.208
My mom asks, "When you think we're gonna
find Steve?" I'm like, "Soon, probably."

08:20.291 --> 08:22.043
And then she asks me if I want ice cream.

08:22.126 --> 08:23.503
That's 'cause that's what she wants.

08:23.586 --> 08:25.588
And then I go get the ice cream.
I bring it back.

08:25.671 --> 08:27.548
She cries 'cause I'm not Steve.

08:28.591 --> 08:30.051
And then I eat the ice cream.

08:30.718 --> 08:33.846
-Oh, yeah. That sounds unhealthy.
-Yeah. It is.

08:34.222 --> 08:37.058
I put on 4 LBs. All in my butt.

08:37.808 --> 08:41.145
Well, lots of stairs here,
so you can work that off.

08:41.229 --> 08:43.356
Yeah. My parents are just spiraling,
you know,

08:43.439 --> 08:45.733
and now they're starting
to talk about offering a reward.

08:46.359 --> 08:47.693
[Charlie] A reward for what?

08:48.236 --> 08:49.779
Charlie, not now.

08:49.862 --> 08:53.741
Oh. For anyone that just might know
anything about where my brother could be.

08:54.784 --> 08:56.619
You know, I just feel like...
Don't you feel like...

08:57.078 --> 08:59.830
a reward is just really
a slippery slope, you know?

08:59.914 --> 09:01.040
-[Ben] Yeah.
-Because then it's like giving,

09:01.123 --> 09:03.000
like, a megaphone to all the crazies

09:03.084 --> 09:04.919
so they can just be like,
"Yeah, I've seen him."

09:05.002 --> 09:06.837
-[Ben] Yeah.
-You know, "Down at the mart."

09:06.921 --> 09:09.298
-[Charlie] How much of a reward?
-Charlie, seriously!

09:09.674 --> 09:11.634
-[scoffs]
-[vibrating]

09:11.717 --> 09:14.220
Oh. Oh, I gotta get this.

09:14.303 --> 09:16.305
-Oh, yeah, no problem.
-Um, excuse me.

09:23.688 --> 09:25.523
[Steve] <i>I know you see me calling, bitch.</i>

09:28.276 --> 09:29.235
[beeps]

09:29.318 --> 09:31.612
[Steve] <i>Come on, Jude,</i>
<i>will you just call me, please?</i>

09:31.696 --> 09:33.698
<i>I-- I'm sorry.</i> <i>I love you.</i>

09:33.781 --> 09:35.491
<i>Will you please, please call me back?</i>

09:35.575 --> 09:36.826
<i>I just need to talk to you.</i>

09:37.201 --> 09:38.160
<i>I need you.</i>

09:38.494 --> 09:39.704
<i>Come on, Jude.</i>

09:39.954 --> 09:41.664
<i>Will you call me back, baby, please?</i>

09:41.747 --> 09:42.582
<i>I love you.</i>

09:43.040 --> 09:44.542
<i>All right? Let's work this out.</i>

09:44.625 --> 09:45.501
<i>I love you.</i>

09:48.838 --> 09:51.340
-[beeps]
-<i>You're not gonna get away with this!</i>

09:51.424 --> 09:52.925
<i>You're no fucking angel.</i>

09:53.009 --> 09:55.511
<i>You can't hide forever,</i>
<i>and when I fucking find you,</i>

09:55.595 --> 09:57.513
<i>I am going to fucking kill you!</i>

09:57.597 --> 10:00.057
<i>You hear me? You are fucking dead!</i>

10:04.729 --> 10:05.605
[sniffles]

10:07.189 --> 10:08.649
Oh, I take it he didn't find you.

10:11.611 --> 10:13.529
[sniffles] No.

10:15.698 --> 10:18.784
Are you at all concerned
about your safety, Miss Hale?

10:20.494 --> 10:21.329
What?

10:21.996 --> 10:23.497
Are you afraid he's gonna hurt you?

10:28.252 --> 10:29.086
No.

10:39.722 --> 10:40.556
Char.

10:42.767 --> 10:43.726
Oh, there you are.

10:44.685 --> 10:45.519
Hey.

10:47.313 --> 10:50.149
Oh, Jesus fucking Christ,
now you're smoking?

10:50.650 --> 10:53.486
-[Charlie] Better than vaping.
-[Jen] God, what is wrong with you?

10:53.569 --> 10:54.612
Everything, apparently.

10:54.695 --> 10:57.281
-What, so now, like, nothing matters?
-Not really.

10:57.365 --> 10:59.742
-Anything I do, you're gonna be mad at me.
-You know what?

11:00.409 --> 11:02.787
I don't want to be mad at you,
okay, Charlie?

11:02.870 --> 11:05.164
So help me out here
and do something fucking right.

11:05.247 --> 11:07.833
It's just a stupid cigarette.
It's not like you never do it.

11:08.626 --> 11:10.628
What? What are you talking about?

11:10.711 --> 11:13.756
