12:13.774 --> 12:14.608
What?

12:15.192 --> 12:16.026
Where?

12:16.360 --> 12:17.403
Um...

12:17.486 --> 12:20.781
I don't know. My dad's friend called
from the station, and, uh...

12:21.490 --> 12:24.160
[shuddering] I'm supposed to go down there
or something.

12:24.660 --> 12:28.414
I-- I don't know how to do this. [sighs]

12:28.539 --> 12:31.000
Do you have anyone
that can go with you or...

12:31.542 --> 12:33.294
No. Um...

12:33.919 --> 12:35.713
It's all right. I can go alone.

12:38.424 --> 12:40.551
No, you shouldn't have to do that.

12:42.386 --> 12:43.596
[sighs]

12:45.014 --> 12:45.848
[Jen] Okay.

12:50.311 --> 12:52.313
[sobbing]

12:53.355 --> 12:54.607
[Ben exhales]

13:09.371 --> 13:10.331
[knocks]

13:12.374 --> 13:15.002
Excuse me, ma'am,
you can't be doing that stuff here,

13:15.669 --> 13:17.004
unless you're gonna share.

13:18.130 --> 13:19.465
-Sure.
-[laughs]

13:19.548 --> 13:21.550
But you have to step into my office.

13:31.685 --> 13:33.270
[slow tempo music playing]

13:33.395 --> 13:37.316
Oh, fuck, yes! This song is the best.
[blows smoke]

13:38.150 --> 13:41.278
Actually, no, never mind.
I have never heard this song in my life.

13:41.362 --> 13:43.155
[laughing]

13:43.239 --> 13:46.742
Wait, you're not up on
whatever kind of music this is?

13:46.826 --> 13:47.785
Apparently not.

13:48.452 --> 13:49.703
It's stuck on AM.

13:50.454 --> 13:51.914
But it's very comforting.

13:52.790 --> 13:54.250
-I could see that.
-Yeah.

13:56.418 --> 13:58.546
I'm sorry I ran off last night.

13:58.838 --> 14:00.089
Oh, no, don't...

14:00.464 --> 14:01.298
No stress.

14:01.799 --> 14:04.134
I'm just, uh, I'm sorry you had to go.

14:05.219 --> 14:06.887
I was having a really good time.

14:07.263 --> 14:08.472
Yeah, me too.

14:10.182 --> 14:11.976
And then Jen had an emergency, so--

14:12.059 --> 14:13.269
Is everything okay?

14:14.562 --> 14:15.771
Um...

14:16.355 --> 14:17.648
No...

14:19.525 --> 14:20.734
Her son stole a car.

14:21.902 --> 14:23.529
Oh, shit.

14:23.612 --> 14:24.446
Yeah.

14:25.531 --> 14:28.742
So you're <i>that </i>friend, huh?
You're the clutch friend?

14:29.034 --> 14:30.536
Yes, but she is too.

14:30.995 --> 14:32.621
She's, you know...

14:33.289 --> 14:38.460
She's great. She took me in
when I was kinda in between places.

14:39.587 --> 14:42.798
-So you guys, uh, live together?
-Mm-hmm.

14:44.717 --> 14:46.844
And you're just friends?

14:46.927 --> 14:48.387
Oh, just friends, yeah.

14:49.722 --> 14:51.473
'Cause you're not, uh...

14:51.849 --> 14:52.850
Not with her.

14:57.313 --> 15:00.065
-Is this the moonstone I gave you?
-Yes, yes.

15:00.149 --> 15:01.609
I thought it looked pretty like this.

15:02.443 --> 15:03.360
It does.

15:04.486 --> 15:06.030
It looks really pretty on you.

15:07.197 --> 15:08.032
Thank you.

15:13.913 --> 15:15.664
Should we, um...

15:17.082 --> 15:18.000
maybe...

15:20.169 --> 15:21.545
go get some tacos?

15:24.506 --> 15:26.675
[scoffs] Yeah.

15:27.134 --> 15:30.679
-I am fucking starving.
-[laughing]

15:30.763 --> 15:32.765
[engine turns over]

15:33.432 --> 15:35.851
[siren wailing]

16:05.923 --> 16:06.757
It's not him.

16:07.299 --> 16:08.759
-[both sigh]
-It's not?

16:08.842 --> 16:10.928
Mr. Wood, I know your family
has connections here,

16:11.011 --> 16:12.721
but everyone needs to follow protocol.

16:12.805 --> 16:13.806
Are you sure it's not him?

16:15.599 --> 16:17.977
Forensics just determined
the remains belonged to a female.

16:18.060 --> 16:19.061
-Oh, that's great.
-[sighs]

16:19.478 --> 16:22.523
I mean, uh...
a great tragedy for her family.

16:23.315 --> 16:24.817
[Ben] Yeah. Uh...

16:24.900 --> 16:26.944
-Thank you, Detective.
-Yes, thank you.

16:28.195 --> 16:29.947
I'm sorry.
How do you two know each other?

16:30.447 --> 16:32.074
Oh, I'm helping him find a rental.

16:32.157 --> 16:34.743
-Yeah, Steve's ex introduced us.
-Mm-hmm.

16:35.119 --> 16:35.953
Judy Hale?

16:36.829 --> 16:38.872
-You know Judy?
-I do.

16:38.956 --> 16:40.582
-It's a small town.
-No, it's not.

16:40.666 --> 16:42.334
Ehhh.

16:43.794 --> 16:46.839
Hi, may I have two salmon tacos,

16:46.922 --> 16:48.507
uh, two chicken,

16:48.590 --> 16:50.509
two tofu mushroom burgers?

16:50.592 --> 16:51.468
That's too much.

16:51.552 --> 16:54.179
-Accept your destiny, please.
-[laughs]

16:54.346 --> 16:57.099
Um, one beef burrito, uh...

16:57.182 --> 17:00.561
carnitas nachos, loaded,
and one large guac.

17:00.644 --> 17:02.229
And two Mexican Cokes, please.

17:03.439 --> 17:04.606
That was masterful.

17:04.690 --> 17:06.608
-No, no, I got it.
-[bottles pop open]

17:06.692 --> 17:07.609
Thank you.

17:07.693 --> 17:09.111
[Michelle] Here. Keep the change.

17:09.737 --> 17:10.571
[Judy] Thank you.

17:11.030 --> 17:13.490
[sighs] I love a Mexican Coke.

17:13.574 --> 17:14.992
-Aren't they so much better?
-The best.

17:15.075 --> 17:16.535
-They're real sugar.
-Yes, that's why.

17:16.618 --> 17:18.328
I can't believe
you haven't been here before.

17:18.412 --> 17:20.456
-[Nick] Best tacos in Laguna.
-[gags]

17:20.539 --> 17:23.292
-Are you okay?
-Yeah, I just choked for a second.

17:23.375 --> 17:24.334
-Hmm.
-[Judy] This Coke.

17:25.044 --> 17:26.253
-Hey, Nick.
-Hey.

17:26.336 --> 17:28.464
My God, it's great to see you.

17:28.547 --> 17:30.007
[scoffs] Is it?

17:31.216 --> 17:32.342
Hi, I'm Michelle.

17:33.385 --> 17:34.803
-What's up?
-Hi.

17:34.887 --> 17:36.680
How are-- how are you doing?

17:37.264 --> 17:39.600
Well, I left my house today,

17:39.683 --> 17:42.061
so that's a start.

17:43.520 --> 17:44.354
How's...

17:45.105 --> 17:46.482
How's Steve?

17:46.565 --> 17:47.900
-[gags, clears throat]
-[Nick] How's he?

17:47.983 --> 17:49.485
He's, uh...

17:49.610 --> 17:51.028
Who's Steve?

17:51.111 --> 17:54.114
-Oh, that's her boyfriend.
-No. He's my ex-boyfriend.

17:54.698 --> 17:58.535
-That didn't work out.
-Yeah. Guess I know how that goes.

18:00.746 --> 18:03.040
-Hey, it was really nice to meet you.
-You too.

18:03.457 --> 18:04.875
-[Judy] Take care.
-[slurps] Mm.

18:08.378 --> 18:09.213
Drive safely.

18:12.925 --> 18:15.844
-What the fuck was that?
-[sighs] Yeah, right?

18:17.513 --> 18:18.347
-Weird.
-[bell dings]

18:18.430 --> 18:19.848
-[woman] Order's up.
-Oh, that's us.

18:21.850 --> 18:24.645
-[sighs]
-Well, that was a relief, huh?

18:24.728 --> 18:26.188
-Yeah, yeah.
-Yeah.

18:28.816 --> 18:31.235
-[crying]
-Oh. Oh, God, Ben.

18:32.653 --> 18:34.154
-Ben.
-I'm sorry.

18:34.238 --> 18:36.240
It's okay. You don't have to apologize.

18:36.698 --> 18:38.117
I just thought, you know...

18:39.076 --> 18:41.495
I thought for sure it was gonna be Steve.
[sighs]

18:42.788 --> 18:44.456
Well, it wasn't him.

18:44.790 --> 18:47.334
No, I know, but for a minute there,
I thought it was...

18:47.835 --> 18:49.878
I thought it was gonna be him. [exhales]

18:49.962 --> 18:52.673
[inhales] Ooh, God, I feel sick.

18:53.632 --> 18:55.968
-Oh, this is a terrible feeling.
-Mm-hmm.

18:56.051 --> 18:58.387
[sighs, sniffles]

18:58.470 --> 19:00.514
I don't know how people live
with that feeling.

19:02.141 --> 19:04.309
Well, you don't have a choice.

19:04.560 --> 19:06.937
You just learn to cope.

19:10.274 --> 19:11.108
Yeah.

19:13.152 --> 19:14.403
Thank you for coming with me.

19:14.486 --> 19:16.697
I know this is not how you wanted
to spend your afternoon,

19:16.780 --> 19:18.657
-at a police station.
-Oh, it's okay.

19:18.991 --> 19:21.410
You're a very kind realtor.<i> </i>[laughs]

19:21.493 --> 19:22.536
Can I, um...

19:22.619 --> 19:24.705
pay you back with a mocktail? [chuckles]

19:24.830 --> 19:26.790
Oh, uh, I-- I can't.

19:27.207 --> 19:29.459
Yours doesn't have to be a mock,
it can be a cock...

19:29.543 --> 19:30.377
Cocktail.

19:31.086 --> 19:34.548
No, I got it.
Uh, no, actually, I have to go.

19:34.631 --> 19:37.134
My son is singing his first solo
with his...

19:38.051 --> 19:39.303
Always so hard to say.

19:39.386 --> 19:41.388
...his Christian rock choral group.

19:43.182 --> 19:44.016
Wait.

19:44.600 --> 19:46.727
Are you talking about the Holy Harmonies?

19:48.020 --> 19:49.104
Why do you know that?

19:49.730 --> 19:50.606
[laughs]

19:51.773 --> 19:55.110
Holy Harmonizer, '86 through '89.

19:55.652 --> 19:57.571
-Really?
-Yes. [laughs]

19:57.654 --> 19:59.239
Actually, I'm not surprised by that.

19:59.323 --> 20:02.451
Wow, that's great!
Oh, I'd love to see that.

20:02.534 --> 20:06.788
I mean, not that, you know,
I'm self-inviting or anything.

20:07.414 --> 20:08.790
You are, though, aren't you?

20:09.416 --> 20:11.043
-I mean, it's been a while.
-Okay.

20:11.126 --> 20:13.545
-The more the merrier.
-And...

20:14.004 --> 20:15.172
-Really?
-Sure.

20:15.255 --> 20:18.967
Oh, fantastic news. [sighs]

20:19.384 --> 20:20.719
-My cup of tizzle.
-Mm-hmm.

20:22.095 --> 20:24.348
Well, we only dated for a little bit.

20:25.307 --> 20:28.268
He's actually really sweet.
Just didn't end so great.

20:28.644 --> 20:30.062
[laughs] Yeah, that was obvious.

20:30.687 --> 20:33.023
-I feel like I'm gonna need the story.
-[groans]

20:33.565 --> 20:36.026
The story doesn't really paint me
in the greatest light.

20:36.443 --> 20:37.945
Well, now I want to hear more.

20:41.490 --> 20:45.535
I thought I was pregnant
with someone else's baby.

20:46.203 --> 20:47.829
-Oh, okay.
-Yeah.

20:49.414 --> 20:50.457
But I wasn't.

20:51.124 --> 20:52.542
It turns out that, um...

20:53.710 --> 20:56.421
I can't have kids, actually.

20:58.090 --> 20:58.966
I'm sorry.

20:59.967 --> 21:00.801
Thanks.

21:01.260 --> 21:03.262
Is that something you really wanted?

21:03.345 --> 21:04.179
Yeah.

21:04.888 --> 21:05.931
Yeah, very much.

21:07.641 --> 21:08.475
Yeah, me too.

21:09.268 --> 21:10.811
I always wanted to adopt, but...

21:11.520 --> 21:13.063
my ex didn't want kids.

21:14.064 --> 21:15.565
Maybe the next person will.

21:16.900 --> 21:17.901
Yeah, maybe.

21:23.740 --> 21:26.618
I still live with her, which is a thing.

21:28.203 --> 21:29.121
Your ex?

21:29.204 --> 21:30.163
Yeah.

21:30.247 --> 21:32.082
I mean, we broke up a while ago,

21:32.165 --> 21:33.208
uh, but...

21:34.334 --> 21:36.628
I couldn't just cut and run.
I mean, she...

21:37.796 --> 21:41.717
she grew up in foster care,
and she has... abandonment stuff.

21:42.509 --> 21:45.762
We're more like family than anything else
at this point, but...

21:46.430 --> 21:48.181
I don't know,
I hope that doesn't sound weird.

21:49.516 --> 21:51.435
I think it sounds really sweet.

21:55.272 --> 21:57.190
-Would you wanna--
-You wanna go see a kids' Christian choir?

21:57.274 --> 21:58.525
[laughs]

21:58.608 --> 22:01.194
Wow, well, I was gonna say
go see a movie,

22:01.278 --> 22:03.363
but what you just said is weirder.

22:03.739 --> 22:05.657
So... yeah.

22:07.117 --> 22:08.785
-Let's do that.
-Yeah.

22:08.869 --> 22:11.413
-[pop music playing]
-[audience cheering]

22:15.000 --> 22:18.420
<i>♪ Like a fool I went and stayed too long ♪</i>

22:19.671 --> 22:22.215
<i>♪ Now I'm wondering</i>
<i>If your love's too strong ♪</i>

22:22.299 --> 22:24.593
<i>♪ Ooh, Jesus ♪</i>

22:24.676 --> 22:28.555
<i>♪ Here I am, signed, sealed, delivered</i>
<i>I'm yours ♪</i>

22:32.601 --> 22:34.644
<i>♪ Then that time I went... ♪</i>

22:34.728 --> 22:36.146
How badly do you want to run up there

22:36.229 --> 22:37.105
-and join them?
-So badly!

22:37.189 --> 22:40.192
<i>♪ Now I'm back and not ashamed to cry ♪</i>

22:40.275 --> 22:41.860
<i>♪ Ooh, Jesus ♪</i>

22:42.402 --> 22:43.528
<i>-♪ Here I am ♪</i>
<i>-</i>Wow!

22:43.612 --> 22:46.198
<i>♪ Signed, sealed, delivered, I'm yours ♪</i>

22:49.076 --> 22:51.078
<i>♪ Here I am, Jesus ♪</i>

22:52.329 --> 22:55.957
<i>♪ Signed, sealed, delivered</i>
<i>I'm yours, Jesus ♪</i>

22:56.416 --> 22:57.292
Hey!

22:57.584 --> 23:00.337
<i>♪ Here I am, Jesus ♪</i>

23:01.171 --> 23:05.217
<i>♪ Signed, sealed, delivered</i>
<i>I'm yours, Jesus... ♪</i>

23:11.348 --> 23:14.017
Yeah, this is even weirder than I thought.

23:14.101 --> 23:16.603
-[laughs]
-I mean, but it is cute.

23:17.145 --> 23:18.522
Oh, wait till you see Henry.

23:21.691 --> 23:22.526
Hey.

23:23.026 --> 23:26.238
-Can I speak to you stage right?
<i>-♪ Ooh, Jesus ♪</i>

23:26.321 --> 23:28.323
<i>♪ Here I am, signed, sealed... ♪</i>

23:28.407 --> 23:31.576
-What's going on, huh?
<i>-</i>Henry's having some show night jitters.

23:31.660 --> 23:33.662
Oh, I'm sure he's just nervous
'cause he has a solo.

23:33.745 --> 23:35.747
I think he's still upset
about what my dog did to his bird,

23:35.831 --> 23:37.541
but we're sending Adele to boot camp
as we speak.

23:37.624 --> 23:39.042
-Why?
-I don't know how to discipline.

23:39.126 --> 23:40.710
I've only ever had two rules in my house:

23:40.794 --> 23:42.879
smoke out the windows
and don't bring Prosecco.

23:42.963 --> 23:44.589
Adele didn't kill the bird.

23:45.132 --> 23:46.466
-What?
-Shandy did it.

23:46.550 --> 23:49.928
Which, looking back,
seems like it was right there.

23:50.345 --> 23:52.973
-I thought I told you.
-No, you did not. Jen!

23:53.056 --> 23:54.641
Adele is halfway to Oxnard.

23:54.724 --> 23:58.437
God. Well, maybe she'll pick up
some good habits or something.

23:59.146 --> 24:01.106
[sighs] Hey.

24:02.149 --> 24:03.024
What's going on?

24:05.485 --> 24:06.528
It's okay, tell her.

24:08.989 --> 24:09.990
Tell me what, hon?

24:11.700 --> 24:14.327
He doesn't want to do it.
It's too much for him, but...

24:14.494 --> 24:16.538
he's scared that
you're gonna be mad, so...

24:17.038 --> 24:20.876
Oh, Boop, I'm not mad.

24:21.710 --> 24:24.254
I thought I had to.

24:24.379 --> 24:26.131
-[Christopher] Um...
-[Jen] Hmm?

24:26.214 --> 24:29.968
Honestly, this is for the best.
He hasn't exactly found his falsetto.

24:32.012 --> 24:32.846
[Jen] Okay, look.

24:33.263 --> 24:35.640
Let's forget the have-to's. Okay?

24:36.725 --> 24:37.976
What do you want to do?

24:41.146 --> 24:42.689
[rock music playing]

24:43.106 --> 24:46.318
-Whoo-hoo! Yeah!
-[siren blaring]

24:46.860 --> 24:49.863
<i>♪ Fun times, it's what the world needs ♪</i>

24:49.946 --> 24:52.199
<i>♪ Fun times, we got a reason to play ♪</i>

24:52.282 --> 24:54.201
-No, no, no!
-No, I'm good at this game!

24:54.284 --> 24:55.368
[laughing]

24:56.369 --> 24:59.039
[game buttons clicking]

24:59.122 --> 25:00.790
[chimes]

25:01.333 --> 25:02.417
Fuck, yeah!

25:03.001 --> 25:05.003
-[Judy] Look at you on your Harley!
-[Michelle] Wow!

25:05.086 --> 25:07.339
[camera shutter clicking]

25:09.633 --> 25:12.636
-[laughing]
-[Michelle] Oh.

25:12.719 --> 25:16.973
Well, it is very nice to meet you,
new friend Michelle.

25:17.057 --> 25:20.060
Likewise.
Judy speaks very, very highly of you.

25:20.143 --> 25:23.063
-'Cause I know all of her secrets.
-[laughing]

25:23.688 --> 25:27.484
Can I get anybody a drink
so that I can begin to drink?

25:27.567 --> 25:30.153
Yes, please. Thank you.
Um, I'll take a Chardonnay.

25:30.237 --> 25:31.738
-Yeah, me, too. Please.
-Great.

25:31.821 --> 25:33.657
I will get two bottles, just to be safe.

25:33.740 --> 25:34.950
Oh, yes. Thank you.

25:38.245 --> 25:39.329
You like her.

25:39.746 --> 25:40.664
I do.

25:41.623 --> 25:43.083
She makes me feel really good.

25:45.001 --> 25:47.837
-You deserve that.
-Thanks.

25:47.921 --> 25:49.172
She seems great.

25:49.589 --> 25:51.049
She's got a very nice energy.

25:51.716 --> 25:54.386
What, did you just comment
on someone's energy?

25:54.469 --> 25:55.303
Nope.

25:55.387 --> 25:56.805
-I'm pretty sure I heard that.
-Nope.

25:56.888 --> 25:58.348
-"Nice energy."
-Don't get excited.

25:58.431 --> 26:01.059
-Uh-huh. [laughs]
-Didn't happen.

26:01.851 --> 26:02.686
It did.

26:02.769 --> 26:05.355
She's getting me booze,
and she suggested two bottles.

26:05.438 --> 26:07.399
-She's really funny--
-So what is she gonna get for herself?

26:07.941 --> 26:09.401
[both laugh]

26:09.901 --> 26:10.819
All right.

26:10.902 --> 26:12.904
[Ben] Go, go, go, go!

26:13.488 --> 26:15.407
Oh, we got a tight one.
This is a nail biter.

26:15.490 --> 26:16.408
[Henry] I know. Yes!

26:16.992 --> 26:19.995
-[Henry claps]
-Whoo! Hey, third!

26:20.078 --> 26:20.996
Look who won.

26:21.705 --> 26:24.874
Nicely done.
Nice. How's your pinball game?

26:24.958 --> 26:26.126
I'm pretty good at pinball.

26:26.209 --> 26:28.253
Yeah? Strong? All right. Let's find one.

26:29.838 --> 26:30.922
[presses buttons]

26:32.966 --> 26:34.342
-Hey. What? What's up?
-Hey.

26:38.513 --> 26:40.140
I'm gonna put your door back on.

26:40.974 --> 26:42.309
Just don't have sex in there.

26:42.892 --> 26:46.855
Or do. I-- It's better than a car,
I don't know. Just...

26:48.565 --> 26:49.774
Just protect yourself.

26:50.900 --> 26:52.152
Always get consent.

26:54.237 --> 26:55.697
-Yep.
-Okay?

26:56.489 --> 26:57.324
Okay.

26:59.659 --> 27:02.245
[game sounds blaring]

27:09.002 --> 27:09.919
[static crackles]

27:10.003 --> 27:12.547
[women speaking indistinctly
over police scanner]

27:31.066 --> 27:34.611
[shouts] Oh, yeah. All right, okay..

27:35.403 --> 27:38.406
-[Henry] Are you letting me win?
-[Charlie laughs] Uh, maybe...

27:42.702 --> 27:43.536
What?

27:44.704 --> 27:46.039
Oh, um...

27:46.498 --> 27:49.000
I just remembered I should
write you a check for that rental.

27:49.084 --> 27:50.460
Oh, I'm not letting you take that place.

27:51.920 --> 27:55.048
No, you shouldn't be paying oceanfront
prices when you hate the beach.

27:56.132 --> 27:57.008
Just...

27:57.717 --> 27:59.386
You wanna like what you're looking at.

28:00.053 --> 28:02.347
Yeah, yeah. Yeah, you do.

28:02.430 --> 28:04.015
["I Think We're Alone Now" by Tiffany
playing]

28:04.099 --> 28:06.726
<i>♪ The beating of our hearts</i>
<i>Is the only sound ♪ </i>

28:13.149 --> 28:14.109
[Ben clears throat]

28:15.527 --> 28:18.613
<i>♪ Look at the way... ♪</i>

28:19.572 --> 28:22.283
-[both] Cheers.
-[camera shutter clicks]

28:22.659 --> 28:25.620
<i>♪ 'Cause what would they say? ♪</i>

28:27.205 --> 28:29.290
-[both laugh]
-[camera shutter clicks]

28:29.374 --> 28:31.418
<i>♪ Running just as fast as we can ♪</i>

28:32.961 --> 28:35.755
<i>♪ Holding on to one another's hand ♪ </i>

28:36.715 --> 28:39.968
<i>♪ Trying to get away into the night ♪</i>

28:40.051 --> 28:41.928
<i>♪ And then you put your arms around me ♪</i>

28:42.011 --> 28:44.889
<i>♪ And we tumble to the ground</i>
<i>And then you say ♪</i>

28:44.973 --> 28:46.891
<i>♪ I think we're alone now ♪</i>

28:47.726 --> 28:51.521
<i>♪ There doesn't seem to be anyone around ♪</i>

28:52.063 --> 28:54.232
<i>♪ I think we're alone now ♪</i>

28:54.983 --> 28:58.820
<i>♪ The beating of our hearts</i>
<i>Is the only sound ♪</i>

28:59.696 --> 29:01.698
<i>♪ I think we're alone now ♪</i>

29:02.449 --> 29:06.035
<i>♪</i> <i>There doesn't seem to be anyone around ♪</i>

29:06.995 --> 29:08.997
<i>♪ I think we're alone now ♪</i>

29:09.831 --> 29:14.043
<i>♪ The beating of our hearts</i>
<i>Is the only sound ♪</i>

29:28.475 --> 29:30.935
